The `simp only` calls were certainly generated by `simp?`. Is it possible to adjust some simp prorities to make sure that `simp?` calls correspond to the shorter versions you're using in the PR?
I think I prefer the spelling with `intro s hs` than the spelling with `fun`, as it doesn't mix term mode and tactic mode. Same thing below.

```suggestion
protected lemma add (h1 : μ₁ ≪ ν) (h2 : μ₂ ≪ ν') : μ₁ + μ₂ ≪ ν + ν' := by
  intro s hs
```

```suggestion
lemma add_right (h1 : μ ≪ ν) (ν' : Measure α) : μ ≪ ν + ν' := by
  intro s hs
```
